@Node "History"

@{b}Program History:
----------------@{ub}

21st September 1991.     Finished Dear Diary V0.1 Slow and Crap;(.

Sometime in Winter 1992. Finished Dear Diary V1.0 It Looked a lot better
                         but unfortunatly was full of bugs.

15th January 1993.    *  Finished Dear Diary II. I had totally rewritten
  *Major Update*        all it's code and added a text editor to it.
                         It is now VERY FAST and as far as I know is Bugless.


5th October 1995      +  Changed the Diary Editor to accept the fixed Width
   Version 3.0           font "slant 8" to make it look more attractive.
 *Major Update*
                      +  Dear Diary will now install to a Hard drive properly
                         as requested by my ONLY/SINGULAR Registered user.

                      +  It comes equipted with an installer script to make
                         things even easier.

                      +  Intro screen replaced with a much better one!
                         Pointless but I wonder if AMOS programmers know
                         how I did it, because in theory it shouldn't work!
                         I have deliberatly screwed up the screen to create
                         static!

                      +  Redone all of the Graphics code to make it look a
                         lot better and more professional.

                      !  Fixed bug in loading

                      !  Fixed bug in date (again)

                      !  Fixed millions of other little things while I was
                         at it;-)


-----------------------------End of program History-------------------------
@endnode

